Nicole Kidman has been slammed by an American union representing 25,000 flight attendants for her new ad campaign with Etihad Airways . 
  The Association of Professional Flight Attendants argues the deal was at odds with Kidman's role as a United Nations Women's Goodwill Ambassador  . 
  The actress stars in Etihad's new 'Hollywood Glamour' global brand campaign . 
  Etihad has rejected the allegation and says it fully supports its cabin crew during and after pregnancies . 
 